    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Canopies that are relatively small in size and movable, or that fold or collapse into a format and size that is small enough to be portable. Used as a shelter or protection from the sun outdoors, and in religious ceremonies, triumphal entries, or otherwise to shelter or designate a dignitary.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
